For time t = a + 1 week and subsequent times, the inoperability level is computed in the same manner until time t = b week when the effect of the new perturbation is over. At time t = b + 1 week, the effect of the new perturbation dissipates, and the subsequent inoperability path follows a decaying trend as sectors regain progressively their pre-disaster state. Then, from time t = b + 1 week and subsequent time increments, inoperability level is calculated using DIIM as follows:7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
